O my God, ſaith he in ver. 6. of that Pſalme, my ſoule is caſt downe within me, (no queſtion but for the abſence of Gods favour, ver. 7. My rocke, Why haſt thou forgotten me
      ••
   ) therefore (ſaith he) will I remember thee. Remember him, O David? What incouragements ſo to doe? Thy Rock ſeemeth to forget thee, and all his waves and billowes are gone over thee, thou art in a toſſed, and forgotten condition, and yet thou ſayeſt, I will remember thee. Now ſee ver. 8. Yet the Lord will command his loving kindneſſe in the day time, and in the night his ſong ſhall be with me, and my prayer unto the God of my life.
